social_posts.post_text: Got to hang with a legend and pioneer @pauloxistoofficial of @sepultura 🙏

Buenos Aires, I can’t thank you enough for the energy you bring to our shows. To have the entire audience sing as loud as the PA is such an electrifying feeling. Absolutely one of my favorite places in the world to perform in. I can’t wait to come back already. 🙏🏽
Santiago Chile, unbelievable crowd! I can’t wait to come back to South America. Easily some of the best crowds. Muchísimas gracias Santiago. 🙌🏽

Re-Mixing the Parrhesia album in Dolby Atmos was a completely new and exciting experience. Atmos has the ability to make the listener feel immersed into the mix and experience the music from literally all directions. It truly is a new era for music.

You can listen on all streaming platforms that allow Dolby Atmos or Spatial Audio. 

Big thanks to @shawndealey @xomblies @sweetwaterstudios @sweetwatersound and #danieldoss for being a part of the Dolby Atmos mixing process. #animalsasleaders #sumeriabrecords

Paloma 🕊️ 

Paloma is a baby girl name of Mexican origin. Derived from the Latin word palumbus, Paloma means “dove.” Fans of Greek mythology will associate doves with the goddess of love, Aphrodite. According to Ancient Greeks, these delicate birds soared beautifully through the sky, symbolizing grace and serenity. 

Also there was a park in DC where I grew up called “El Parque De Las Palomas” I prob got robbed in it cuz it was kinda hood then but it’s still nostalgic or whatever🤷🏻‍♂️☺️

Also it’s a tequila cocktail 🍹 🎊🥳👶🏻

Also it’s Spanish slang for 🍆
I didn’t make it up. 

The song yes but that last double meaning no. FYI 💙
